Sentencas: We have successfully fabricated a dense-type Scandia-stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) thin-film electrolyte with thickness down to similar to 4 mu m for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs; 600-800 degrees C) by a wet powder spraying technique.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: With an anode-supported design and a La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.1Mn0.9O3 (LSScM) oxide cathode, a peak power density of 788 mW cm(-2) was achieved at 800 degrees C for a cell operating on hydrogen fuel.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The impedance results demonstrated that the electrode polarization resistance is the main source of electrochemical performance loss for the single cell.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta + Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (BSCF + SDC) composite cathode was then applied to improve the cell power output.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: An SDC interlayer was adopted to avoid the interfacial phase reaction between ScSZ and BSCF, which was also fabricated by the wet powder spraying.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: The effect of interlayer processing on the morphology and cell performance was studied by SEM-EDX, I-V polarization and EIS.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: Pre-sintering of the ScSZ layer was found to be superior to the co-sintering of SDC interlayer and ScSZ electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte

Sentencas: An anode-supported cell with SDC interlayer fabricated on pre-sintered ScSZ electrolyte film and a BSCF + SDC cathode delivered a peak power density as high as 1760 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees
Titulo: Wet powder spraying fabrication and performance optimization of IT-SOFCs with thin-film ScSZ electrolyte
